{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GFXUBC7rWRctfEGiuH37S9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup:\n- CockroachDB cluster running in insecure mode with `--insecure` flag\n- 3 nodes: crdb-cluster-0, crdb-cluster-1, crdb-cluster-2\n- An openssl-toolbox pod for certificate generation\n- No existing secrets/certs\n\nTo enable TLS, I need to:\n1. Generate certificates using the openssl-toolbox pod:\n   - CA certificate and key\n   - Node certificates for each node (crdb-cluster-0, crdb-cluster-1, crdb-cluster-2)\n   - Client certificate for the root user\n2. Create Kubernetes secrets to store these certificates\n3. Update the StatefulSet to mount the cert secrets, remove the `--insecure` flag, add the certs directory path, and switch the health probes to HTTPS\n\nI'll start by generating the CA certificate and key in a temporary directory on the openssl-toolbox pod, then create certificates for each node.\n\nActually, I need to be more careful here—CockroachDB has specific certificate requirements. It needs a CA cert, node certificates with SANs for all node addresses, and client certificates for root access. The standard approach would be to use the `cockroach cert` command, but since I'm working through the openssl-toolbox, I should use standard TLS certificates that follow CockroachDB's naming conventions.\n\nFor the node certificate, the SANs need to cover the pod DNS names like `crdb-cluster-0.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local`, plus `localhost` and `127.0.0.1`. I'm thinking through whether to use a single shared node cert for all nodes or generate separate ones per node.\n\nActually, let me use the `cockroach cert` command directly from one of the pods since CockroachDB is already installed there, rather than relying on the openssl-toolbox pod.\n\nGenerating certificates with cockroach cert... with `ca.crt`, `node.crt`, and `node.key`, plus a separate secret for the root client containing `ca.crt`, `client.root.crt`, and `client.root.key`. Then I'll update the StatefulSet to remove the insecure flag, mount the certs at the proper directory, switch the health probes to HTTPS, and let the pods restart. I also need to make sure the certificate directory has the right permissions for CockroachDB to read them.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1929,"cache_read_input_tokens":29324,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1929},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d7a97e95-9f7d-43e2-8d1d-4df42241feb7","uuid":"c2ba8776-af83-45b6-bb19-dad95ca05a78","request_id":"req_011CcMPsv9p4WvG9YMEZTga5"}
