{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012s4ry4NVNkeQG8mQKeBKb5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue. The pods are restarting but crdb-cluster-2 is not ready yet. Looking at the events:\n- crdb-cluster-0 and crdb-cluster-1 are still running with old revision (they haven't been updated yet due to rolling update)\n- crdb-cluster-2 is the one being updated (new revision `crdb-cluster-6bf58bd7f`) and it's failing the readiness probe with 503\n\nWait, let me look more carefully:\n- crdb-cluster-0: revision `crdb-cluster-9ffc96` (old), 9m39s Running but failing readiness with 503 status\n- crdb-cluster-1: revision `crdb-cluster-9ffc96` (old), 9m39s Running but failing readiness with 503\n- crdb-cluster-2: revision `crdb-cluster-6bf58bd7f` (new), 4m30s Running but failing readiness with 503\n\nActually, the old pods show 1/1 Running which means they're ready, but those readiness events are stale from 4m15s ago. The real issue is that all three pods are currently failing their readiness probes, which is blocking the rollout.\n\nLooking at the revision hashes, crdb-cluster-2 is the only one running the new version while crdb-cluster-0 and crdb-cluster-1 are still on the old revision. The StatefulSet rolling update starts from the highest index, so crdb-cluster-2 got updated first 4m30s ago. The problem is that crdb-cluster-2 is now running in secure mode with TLS certificates, but crdb-cluster-0 and crdb-cluster-1 are still in insecure mode, which is causing the readiness probe failures. then 503 errors with the new HTTPS probe. The 503 responses for the health check are expected when the cluster hasn't been initialized, but since we already initialized in insecure mode, the real problem is that crdb-cluster-2 is now using TLS while the older pods are still running insecurely—this mixed-mode setup is preventing proper cluster communication.\n\nThe rollout is progressing (waiting for pods to become ready), but when a node restarts in secure mode, it can't connect to the insecure nodes. CockroachDB needs a proper migration path for this transition, either through special flags or by initializing in secure mode from the start. Let me check what's actually happening in the crdb-cluster-2 logs to understand the connection failures.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1503,"cache_read_input_tokens":37340,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1503},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d7a97e95-9f7d-43e2-8d1d-4df42241feb7","uuid":"0618b660-b12b-49ec-9ac8-e11e9a9fa918","request_id":"req_011CcMQSSUbUDWK4mQ5Dzjgi"}
